Random notes:

What is the difference between an IP address and a MAC address?
  IP addresses are assigned to devices
  IP - Internet Protocol
  Example of an IP address (32 bits):
    192.168.1.10
  
  MAC addresses are assigned to NIC cards
  MAC - Media Access Control
  Example of a MAC address (6 bits): 
    255.255.255.0
    
Notes about Wireshark:

What is Wireshark?
  Wireshark is an network protocol analyzer which allows users to view packets being sent within their network
 
 What is a network protocol?
  Network protocols are "a set of rules defining a network" (what does this mean?)
